metadata.name: Breakers #280
metadata.description:
Companion project to Neural Collapse (#15780), for the collectors of my previous efforts.
A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple dynamic structure, this time inside a cylinder.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.

Interactivity : 
- You can click on each individual breaker to open or close them. The problem is it will toggle others.
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint. The previous interaction not being disabled while doing that, you get some switching all over the place as a bonus bug/feature.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. If you don't like jaggies and your machine can take it.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

metadata.name: Takashi's Death #209
metadata.description:
Akira by Katsuhiro Otomo.
A global landmark in the shaping of the Cyberpunk genre, and a watershed title for the medium.

I got my hands on the tankōbon(s) more than 20 years ago and those pages upon pages at the end of the third one depicting the destruction of Neo-Tokyo stayed with me ever since. Pages of stunning destruction, leaving me in awe.

This is my generative take on the subject. An attempt to evoke the power of that one panel in a cohesive collection.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.
You can find more info on the composition here : https://ulucode.com/wp/takashis-death/

Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels ( height ). I recommend starting with "4".

More features are available, but a decent GPU is recommended:
- Press "space" to toggle an animation on/off
- Press "u" to Unlock the camera. You can then :
. Mouse left : Rotate
. Mouse middle/wheel : Zoom
. Mouse right : Translate
. "r" : reset camera
. "a" : change antialiasing quality : 3 settings in rotation. Try this if your framerate is too low.

metadata.name: Tumbling Six #11
metadata.description:
Six hollow cubes tumbling through space quietly, enjoying their six degrees of freedom. Only a single machine is there to bear witness. It is Sentinel 31, and its mind wanders. Distracted, it recreates the scene, drawing imaginary lines with an imaginary hand.

~

The original medium of Tumbling Six is the pen plotter. It is entirely vector-based, and can be plotted directly. I use Paper.js to render it on-screen and as SVG, and rely on Three.js for spatial modeling.

~

To generate and download a plottable SVG file, press `S`. Please be patient; this process can take a while. The SVG can be plotted on an A5 paper. The plottable SVG does not include the light grey sketch lines that appear at the start of the animation. Those look nice on screen, but are too much include on paper.

metadata.name: Happenings #209
metadata.description:
Inspired by the chaos and imperfectly beautiful dynamics of parenting and life, 'Happenings' is the embodiment of the messiness, the unexpected and playful experiences that allow for the greatest depths of connection with our children.

Our intention was to evoke our deepest and most personal feelings as parents of young ones navigating the challenges of the pandemic while immersing ourselves in the Web3 arena.

This collection is Jimena + Marcos’ first generative art collection in the Tezos blockchain via FX Hash, and consists of 222 1/1 artworks created with javascript.

metadata.name: Neural Collapse #85
metadata.description:
What happens when your brain overloads, or when you lose control of your giant robot.

A study on the repetition and stacking of a simple but very dynamic structure.

Everything procedurally generated at runtime.
You can find more informations on the piece, its design and origins, here: https://ulucode.com/wp/neural-collapse/

Interactivity : 
- You can hover your mouse on the connectors to close them... temporarily
- Press and hold the mouse button to slightly move the viewpoint.

- Press "a" to increase quality of the antialiasing (3 levels), at the cost of performances. Especially useful on the palettes using outlines.
- Export a PNG capture at various resolutions by pressing the number keys 1 to 9 (top row or numpad, and only in live mode, after pressing "open"). Resolutions ranges from 720 to 7680 pixels. I recommend starting with "4".

GPU recommended. Best performances on Chrome in general.

metadata.name: Deep Forest #73
metadata.description:
I love being in nature and impressionistic paintings. Deep Forest is my latest attempt to combine them with JavaScript. The editions will range from open, sparse forests to lush, dense, leafy wonderlands. Fall editions may render as Klimpt-style birch forests - my original inspiration for this work.

Best viewed on a computer. It may take a few seconds to start drawing and, depending on complexity, several minutes to finish rendering. In live view, press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2318x3000px.

Features:
- One of the four seasons
- Rare 10% night version with 50/50 for normal fireflies or "fire" fireflies. Night will only be spring or summer.
- Amount of atmosphere/haze
- Horizon line near the middle or 30% "high horizon" near the top
- Tint from one of 8 light and 7 shadow colors
- Strength of the light and shadow color tint
- Mixed tree trunks or 30% all birch
- 50/50 moss on tree trunks
- One of 8 flower colors in spring or summer
- One of 4 perspective transforms
- Straight, curved out, or 30% curved inward trunks
- 50/50 grass in fall or winter
- 85% will have flowers in spring and summer
- 95% will have underbrush
- 50/50 clouds or solid background
- 50/50 solid background will be vertical or swirls
- Ground hill height

metadata.name: Chaotic Neutral #222
metadata.description:
'Chaotic Neutral' by pixelwank 
A fun mixture of 10print inspired patterns, spiralling shapes and masking. 

Sometimes more minimal, often chaotic and maximal.

I wanted this work to be confronting at times, make the viewer zoom in and get lost in the chaos. 
And on the flipside, zoom out and let the eyes wander around the piece, guided by the motion of the patterns and feel a sense of calm.

Variety of palettes, grid sizing, strokeweights, blendmodes and more. 

5 possible aspect ratios with 3:4 being most common. 

10% of primary sales are going straight to the Waiting To Be Signed wallet as a donation and thankyou for always delivering great content on the fxhash ecosystem with their podcast <3

50% of royalties to the minter. 
In live mode press 's' or 'S' to save higher resolution image. Contact me via twitter if you want a super hi-res file. 

Copyright pixelwank 2022.
Made with love and p5js 

Thanks for collecting!
Big shoutout to the Circolors fam. Don't worry something's cooking <3 

Remember. It's. For. Fun.
R.I.F.F. 
<3

metadata.name: Pobbles #234
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

• The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
• See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
• Alternative titles considered include Peggles™, Plops™, Blobbies™, Floofs™, Flintstones™, Lardies™, Plumps™, Fats™ and Wet-Ones™. 
• The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
• The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
• They work well with toddlers.

🖨️ Collectors minting at the first auction tier receive a hand-crafted riso print of their pobble. Color variation between the file and the print will apply. 🖨️

metadata.name: Migration #65
metadata.description:
"Migration" is a generative work with which I want to ease my worries about the irresponsibility of people towards the planet they live on.
If we migrate, I hope it will be for the purpose of exploring new areas and not because we have destroyed the planet we live on and are now forced to flee.

Created with 100% p5.js code and math.

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 's' to save .png with resolution = 6000px x 6000px


@Mutart, July, 2022.
